Ryan Gander If I could see but a day of it- (Multiversed) (2008) A hand tufted Persian rug measuring 3 x 2 m reveals a red and white pattern one would usually expect to find on the reverse side of a playing card. A standard pack of double-faced Parallel cards invented by Ryan Gander are placed under the edge of the rug. One of the Queen of Hearts within the pack has been manipulated so that she appears to be winking. Back to artist's page Read full CV Previous / Next